{
  "doc_id": "14935",
  "text": "Epidemiological evidence suggests that left ventricular (LV) failure is a common comorbidity in patients with COPD [CITATION_1] and that outcomes for patients with both LV failure and COPD are worse than those for patients with only COPD. In a long-term study of patients with COPD in Nordic countries, mortality in 36% of patients with COPD was due to cardiovascular causes. In patients with COPD, there is a significant burden of morbidity and mortality related to congestive heart failure, and patients with COPD have been noted to have higher in-hospital mortality.",
