      "span_text": "Epidemiological evidence suggests that left ventricular (LV) failure is a common comorbidity in patients with COPD  and that outcomes for patients with both LV failure and COPD are worse than those for patients with only COPD. In a long-term study of patients with COPD in Nordic countries, mortality in 36% of patients with COPD was due to cardiovascular causes.",
